  "prompt": "Do Las Vegas Casinos pump oxygen into the air conditioning systems? Why?",
  "response": "No, Las Vegas casinos do not pump oxygen into their air conditioning systems. This is actually a common myth. The idea behind it is that higher levels of oxygen could potentially invigorate players and keep them more alert, thus encouraging them to gamble longer. However, there is no concrete evidence to support this practice, and it is not utilized by casinos.\n\nInstead, casinos employ other strategies to attract and retain customers. These can include carefully designed layouts, bright and colorful surroundings, the absence of clocks and windows to obscure the passage of time, comfortable seating, free drinks, and entertainment options. Additionally, casinos often use advanced air filtration systems to maintain a pleasant environment, but they do not enhance oxygen levels artificially for the purpose of stimulating players.",
